LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
HOUSE BILL NO. 84
BY STATE AFFAIRS COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO THE DEPARTMENT OF ADMINISTRATION; AMENDING SECTION 67-5767,
3 IDAHO CODE, TO PROVIDE THAT THE DIRECTOR OF THE DEPARTMENT OF ADMIN-
4 ISTRATION MAY PROVIDE SERVICE TO CITIES AND TO MAKE TECHNICAL CORREC-
5 TIONS; AND DECLARING AN EMERGENCY AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.
6 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
7 SECTION 1. That Section 67-5767, Idaho Code, be, and the same is hereby
8 amended to read as follows:
9 67-5767. DIRECTOR MAY PROVIDE SERVICE TO SCHOOL DISTRICTS, PUBLIC
10 COMMUNITY COLLEGES, PUBLIC COLLEGES, PUBLIC UNIVERSITIES, CITIES, OR OTHER
11 POLITICAL SUBDIVISIONS. (1) Under terms and procedures mutually agreed upon
12 on by contract, the director of the department of administration may render
13 the same services with respect to personnel of any school district, public
14 community college, public college, public university, city, or other po-
15 litical subdivision of the state of Idaho. The cost of any group insurance,
16 group annuity, or health care service coverage so provided and of admin-
17 istration thereof shall be borne by the school district, public community
18 college, public college, public university, city, or other political subdi-
19 vision.
20 (2) Other political subdivision for the purpose of this section means
21 any organization composed of units of government of Idaho or organizations
22 funded only by government or government employee contributions or organiza-
23 tions who discharge governmental responsibilities that would otherwise be
24 performed by government.
25 SECTION 2. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
26 declared to exist, this act shall be in full force and effect on and after
27 July 1, 2025.

